results.name: Number of integer partitions of n not containing 1 or any prime indices of the parts.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798.
example: The a(2) = 1 through a(10) = 9 integer partitions:
xref: The subset version is A324742, with maximal case A324763. The strict case is A324752. The Heinz number version is A324761. An infinite version is A324695.
